# The scroll scene: the scroll viewport's contract — content
# overflows the visible extent (both readings geometry), scroll_end
# drives the toolkit's REAL scrolling API, expect_at_end reads the
# content's end edge back, and the trailing click proves the
# scrolled-to content is live (the bottom button writes the status
# label at the top).
expect_overflow scroll#0
expect label#0 "at top"
scroll_end scroll#0
expect_at_end scroll#0
click button#0
expect label#0 "bottom clicked"
